The paper deals with visual secret sharing schemes, which is a topic related to cryptography and security (cs.CR). The scheme proposed in the paper is specifically designed for grayscale images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the issue of pixel expansion, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). The construction of the shadow images involves binary operations, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes a probabilistic scheme, which is related to statistical learning and inference (cs.SI).
